FBIS4-65417 "drweu096_q_94006" FBIS-WEU-94-096 Daily Report 4 May 1994 TURKEY Ambassadors Receive Intelligence Briefing Ambassadors Receive Intelligence Briefing NC1305155594 Istanbul SABAH in Turkish 4 May 94 p 13 NC1305155594 Istanbul SABAH Turkish BFN [Text] The National Intelligence Organization [NIO] held a briefing for 12 ambassadors and two permanent representatives yesterday. It has been learned that the Turkish ambassadors and permanent representatives, who have arrived to study the situation in southeastern Turkey, were briefed by NIO Under Secretary Sonmez Koksal for nearly four hours. The ambassadors then outlined the problems they have to deal with in Europe. It has also been ascertained that the possibility of beginning a dialogue between the intelligence units and the ambassadors was discussed in the briefing.
